WCS2 Women in Cybersecurity Scholarship 2025
Quick Start Checklist & Key Resources
Congratulations on being awarded the WCS2 Women in Cybersecurity Scholarship!
This scholarship, proudly offered by the Women CyberSecurity Society (WCS2) in
partnership with Google and Coursera, provides you with fully funded access to the
Google Cybersecurity Career Certificate. This guide will help you navigate the
program, understand expectations, and access resources and support throughout your
journey.
Program Structure & Expectations
✅Google Cybersecurity Career Certificate
The program is composed of nine self-paced courses designed to build your
foundational cybersecurity skills. You must complete all nine to earn your
industry-recognized certificate.
1. Foundations of Cybersecurity
2. Play It Safe: Manage Security Risks
3. Connect and Protect: Networks and Network Security
4. Tools of the Trade: Linux and SQL
5. Assets, Threats, and Vulnerabilities
6. Sound the Alarm: Detection and Response
7. Automate Cybersecurity Tasks with Python
8. Put It to Work: Prepare for Cybersecurity Jobs
9. Google Cybersecurity Certificate Capstone
Scholarship Checklist & Resources
✅Step-by-Step Checklist
● Watch your inbox for your Coursera onboarding email (within 24 hours).
● Verify your Coursera account using the same email registered through
WCS2.
● Add WCS2 and Coursera to your safe sender list.
● Begin the 9 courses in the Google Cybersecurity Career Certificate in order.
● Track your progress and stay consistent with your learning schedule.
● Save this guide and your acceptance email for future records.
WCS2 Empowering Women For Cyber™ 1Completion & Recognition
✅How to Receive Your Certificate
To receive your final Google Cybersecurity Career Certificate:
1. Verify your Coursera account with the same email used for onboarding.
2. Complete all nine required courses.
3. Coursera will automatically issue your certificate via email once all
requirements are met.
✅Showcasing Your Certificate
Once awarded, be sure to showcase your achievement by adding the certificate to your
LinkedIn profile, resume, and professional portfolio. This recognition demonstrates
your commitment to advancing in cybersecurity.
✅Graduate Spotlight & Community
WCS2 is proud to spotlight scholarship graduates on our website, newsletters, and
social platforms. By sharing your story, you can inspire other women to pursue
cybersecurity careers. As a graduate, you are also encouraged to join our WCS2 Pro
Membership and explore opportunities for mentorship and volunteering.
WCS2 would love to spotlight your success story to inspire others—watch for an
invitation after you graduate!
Graduate Success Spotlight 💡
How did she do it?
One of our recent graduates shared her best piece of advice for success in the program:
“Dedicating at least 2 hours every day for studies and repeating any course or topic you
don't understand sets you up for success,” she advises future scholarship recipients,
reflecting on the disciplined routine that kept her on track.
✅Completion Reminder
